title: Saudi Arabia’s Oil Supremacy Falters - Wall Street Journal
text:
Saudi Arabia’s Oil Supremacy Falters The world’s biggest crude exporter is rejiggering its long-held strategy of clinging to market share By Google+ Updated March 21, 2017 7:02 a.m. ET 
Saudi Arabia is losing its grip on big oil markets it once dominated amid a deep production cut that has reshaped global petroleum trade routes and benefited rivals like Iran, Russia and the U.S. 
To stomach a steep production cut aimed at putting a floor under oil prices, the world’s biggest crude exporter is conceding ground to American shale producers and hastening a retreat from the U.S., people familiar with current Saudi policy...
